0.title: 2019 Course Equivalency Evaluation Request Form
0.description:
Please use this form if you have a transfer course that does not have a direct equivalency or has an expired date in our Transfer Credit Equivalency Database.

Please note transfer credits are not evaluated for non-degree, graduate, and professional students. Transfer institutions must be AACSB-Accredited for any upper-division business course equivalency requests.

( Note: * Indicates a required field.)

fields.label: Upload a Syllabus for the Course
fields.description: A syllabus is required for any non-UCORE major requirement course evaluation and for all international course evaluations. Please be sure your syllabus contains learning outcomes, textbook(s), and a list of course topics and assignments otherwise it may not be sufficient for review by the academic unit. A syllabus is typically not required for University Common Requirements (UCORE) course equivalency evaluations.

fields.label: HTML Block
fields.content: Note: Please allow two weeks for evaluation request results to be emailed to you and please note that departmental evaluation timeframes may vary. WSU will accept transfer credit for traditional course work you have successfully completed at regionally accredited institutions of higher education. This process does not certify applicability of transfer credit toward degree requirements, which are determined by the academic program you are enrolled at WSU. Students with questions regarding how a transfer equivalency applies toward a WSU degree should consult the WSU catalog or contact transfer@wsu.edu. This information is subject to change.
